<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="49" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/766.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Naval Attaché at Tokyo</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <placeName>Tokyo</placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1911-12-11T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1911-12-07T00:00:00+09:00">undated</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram transmitted to the Secretary of State Dec. 11,
                            1911.]</p>
                        <p>Agreement has been reached between the British and Japanese commanding
                            officers to intervene in China, using Japanese soldiers. Three Japanese
                            divisions ready to move on 24 hours notice. The Austrian Military
                            Attaché is authority for the above.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Shipley.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>